VALUES
(42, 6, 17, 19, 103, 3, 3, NULL, 'Healing and Forgiveness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize healing, with Luke mentioning healing of diseases and Psalms stating ''who healeth all thy diseases.'' This connection highlights the theme of divine healing and forgiveness present in both texts.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 17, 19, 107, 17, 20, 'to be healed of their diseases', 'Healing and Deliverance Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the act of healing and deliverance from affliction. In Luke, people come to Jesus to be healed, while in Psalms, the Lord saves those in distress and heals them.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 17, 40, 4, 23, 25, NULL, 'Healing and Multitudes', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus healing diseases and attracting large crowds. They describe the diverse groups coming to him for healing, highlighting his widespread fame and ministry across regions.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 17, 41, 3, 7, 12, 'a great multitude of people', 'Multitudes Seeking Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize a great multitude of people coming to Jesus from various regions to hear him and seek healing. This connection highlights the widespread impact of Jesus'' ministry and the urgent need for healing among the people.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 17, 41, 7, 24, 31, 'to be healed of their diseases', 'Healing and Gentile Inclusion', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' ministry to those in need, including a great multitude from various regions. The connection highlights the healing aspect of Jesus'' work, particularly with a Gentile woman seeking help for her daughter.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 17, 42, 5, 15, 15, NULL, 'Connection of Healing and Multitudes', 'Both passages emphasize the gathering of great multitudes to hear Jesus and to be healed of their infirmities. This connection highlights the growing fame of Jesus and his role as a healer.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 18, 40, 15, 22, 22, 'vexed with unclean spirits', 'Healing from Unclean Spirits', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of healing from demonic affliction. In Luke, those vexed with unclean spirits are healed, while in Matthew, a woman seeks mercy for her daughter who is ''grievously vexed with a devil.''', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 18, 40, 17, 15, 15, 'vexed', 'Connection of Vexation and Healing', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of being ''vexed'' by afflictions. In Luke, those vexed with unclean spirits are healed, while in Matthew, the father describes his son as ''sore vexed'' due to his condition.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 18, 44, 5, 16, 16, 'vexed with unclean spirits', 'Healing of the Vexed', 'Both passages emphasize the healing of those ''vexed with unclean spirits.'' This connection highlights a continuity in the ministry of healing from Jesus to the apostles.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 19, 40, 14, 36, 36, NULL, 'Healing Through Touch', 'Both passages emphasize the power of touch in healing. In Luke, virtue goes out from Jesus to heal, while in Matthew, touching the hem of his garment results in wholeness.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 19, 41, 3, 10, 10, 'to touch him', 'Healing and Touching Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the act of seeking to touch Jesus for healing. They highlight the crowds'' response to His healing power, indicating a strong connection between the two accounts.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 19, 44, 5, 15, 16, 'healed them all', 'Healing Power of Presence', 'Both passages emphasize the healing power associated with the presence of a holy figure. In Luke, virtue goes out from Jesus to heal, while in Acts, Peter''s shadow is believed to have healing effects.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 19, 41, 5, 30, 30, 'virtue out of him', 'Connection of Healing Virtue', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''virtue'' going out from Jesus, indicating his healing power. In Luke, the multitude seeks to touch him for healing, while in Mark, Jesus recognizes that virtue has left him due to a touch.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 19, 40, 9, 20, 21, NULL, 'Healing Through Touch', 'Both passages emphasize the act of touching Jesus for healing. In Luke, the multitude sought to touch him for healing, while in Matthew, the woman believed that touching his garment would make her whole.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 19, 42, 8, 45, 46, 'virtue out of him', 'Connection of Healing Virtue', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''virtue'' going out from Jesus, highlighting His healing power. In Luke 6:19, the multitude seeks to touch Him for healing, while in Luke 8:45-46, a specific touch results in the release of that same virtue.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 19, 60, 2, 9, 9, 'virtue out of him', 'Healing and Divine Calling', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine intervention and transformation. In Luke, the virtue of Jesus brings healing, while in 1 Peter, believers are called out of darkness into light, emphasizing a change brought by divine power.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 20, 42, 6, 20, 24, 'Blessed be ye poor: for yours is the kingdom of God.', 'Connection of Blessings and Woes', 'Both passages emphasize the contrast between the blessed state of the poor and the woes of the rich. This connection highlights the theme of divine reversal, where those who suffer now are promised future rewards.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 20, 59, 2, 5, 5, 'yours is the kingdom of God', 'Connection of the Poor and Kingdom', 'Both passages emphasize the blessedness of the poor and their inheritance of the kingdom of God. Luke highlights the poor as recipients of the kingdom, while James affirms that God has chosen the poor as heirs rich in faith.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 20, 47, 8, 9, 9, 'Blessed be ye poor', 'Connection of Poverty and Riches', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of poverty leading to spiritual richness. Luke highlights the blessedness of the poor, while 2 Corinthians explains how Christ''s poverty brings richness to believers.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 20, 42, 12, 32, 32, 'yours is the kingdom of God', 'Connection of Kingdom Promises', 'Both passages emphasize the promise of the kingdom, highlighting that it is given to the poor and the faithful. This connection highlights the assurance of God''s favor towards those who may feel marginalized.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 20, 40, 25, 34, 34, 'yours is the kingdom of God', 'Connection of Kingdom Inheritance', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of inheriting the kingdom. Luke highlights the poor as recipients of the kingdom, while Matthew speaks of the blessed inheriting the kingdom prepared for them.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 20, 40, 5, 2, 12, 'Blessed be ye poor', 'Blessed Are the Poor Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the blessedness of the poor, linking their condition to the kingdom of God/heaven. This connection highlights a theme of divine favor towards those in humble circumstances.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 20, 66, 2, 9, 9, 'Blessed be ye poor', 'Blessed Poverty and Riches', 'This connection highlights the theme of poverty in both passages, where the poor are acknowledged in Luke as blessed and in Revelation, the church is recognized for its tribulation and poverty yet deemed rich. Both verses emphasize the paradox of spiritual wealth amidst material lack.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 21, 40, 5, 6, 6, 'hunger now', 'Connection of Blessings and Fulfillment', 'Both passages emphasize a state of hunger and the promise of being filled. Luke speaks of hunger and weeping, while Matthew focuses on hunger and thirst for righteousness, linking the themes of longing and divine fulfillment.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 21, 43, 6, 35, 35, 'hunger now', 'Hunger and Fulfillment', 'This connection highlights the theme of hunger and fulfillment in both passages. Luke speaks of those who hunger being filled, while John presents Jesus as the bread of life, indicating that belief in Him satisfies spiritual hunger.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 21, 59, 1, 12, 12, 'Blessed are ye that weep now', 'Blessings in Trials and Suffering', 'This connection highlights the theme of blessings associated with enduring hardship. Both passages emphasize the promise of fulfillment and joy following current struggles, linking physical and spiritual trials.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 21, 23, 61, 1, 3, 'Blessed are ye that weep now', 'Connection of Comfort and Blessing', 'Both passages emphasize comfort for those who mourn and the promise of joy for the afflicted. Luke 6:21''s ''Blessed are ye that weep now'' resonates with Isaiah 61:2''s call to ''comfort all that mourn.''', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 21, 19, 107, 9, 9, 'hunger now', 'Connection of Hunger and Fulfillment', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of hunger and fulfillment. Luke 6:21 speaks of those who hunger being filled, while Psalms 107:9 states that God fills the hungry soul with goodness.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 21, 23, 55, 1, 2, 'hunger now', 'Connection of Hunger and Thirst', 'This connection highlights the themes of physical and spiritual hunger and thirst. Both passages emphasize the promise of fulfillment and satisfaction for those who seek nourishment, whether it be food or spiritual sustenance.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 21, 42, 1, 53, 53, 'hunger now: for ye shall be filled', 'Connection of Hunger and Fulfillment', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of hunger and fulfillment. Luke 6:21 speaks of the hungry being filled, while Luke 1:53 states, ''He hath filled the hungry with good things.''', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
